cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.ST

The paper discusses the development of an interpretable VAE for grouped data that models complex, nonlinear latent-to-observed relationships. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also applies the model to motion capture and MEG data, which suggests that it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and neuroscience and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of sparsity-inducing priors, which suggests that it may also belong to the statistics (cs.ST) sub-category.
